CMUAnalysis/PhotonLepton Contents

***Read CMUAnalysis/Common/README for more details***

[filter.cc]
This is the function used to produce analysis skims with various selections from the original SUSYNtuples. The skim is given in the simpleTree format, with additional variables in the eventVars tree indicating which event selection the event has passed. The function takes as an input the path to a configuration file. The example configuration is given in filter.cfg. The interface of the function is designed for use within the cmu job scheduler.

[skim.cc]
This is the function to produce generic skims with simple cuts on SUSYNtuples. The arguments are the skim type, triggers, and the path to a lumi list file. The interface of the function is designed for use within the cmu job scheduler.
